                <h3> Universal Basic Income FAQ </h3>

                  <p> <b> Q </b>: How will it be distributed? </p>

                <p> <b> A </b>: Most universal basic income proposals suggest that the money be distributed at scheduled intervals - weekly, monthly, yearly, etc. Some suggest that money be given at one time, say when one turns 18. </p>

                <p> <b> Q </b>: How would it be paid for? </p>

                <p> <b> A </b>:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li> The savings of welfare programs which have been replaced by it. </li>
                    <li> Elimination of Minimum Wage </li>
                    <li> Taxation, specifically on high end consumption and financial transactions</li>
                </ul>

                <p> <b> Q </b>: Would it just cause inflation? </p>

                <p> <b> A </b>: No. This is because no new money is being minted. You can consider it as the shifting of funds and money. </p>

